Segun Omidele has resigned as CEO of dual-listed oil and gas company Erin Energy Corporation, with immediate effect. His departure is expected in the coming weeks, during which time he will assist in the orderly transition of his duties and responsibilities to interim CEO Jean-Michel Malek, who previously served as senior VP, general counsel and secretary. Prior to joining Erin Energy, Malek was with Camac International Corporation, where he served as executive VP and general counsel from January 2011, prior to which he was senior VP and general counsel, since January 2007.